# Vercel Speed Insights Installation Report

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Speed Insights for the Next.js portfolio website.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- **Added dependency**: `@vercel/speed-insights` package
- **Package manager**: npm
- **Files modified**: `package.json`, `package-lock.json`

### 2. Component Integration
- **File modified**: `app/layout.tsx`
- **Changes**:
  - Added import: `import { SpeedInsights } from "@vercel/speed-insights/next";`
  - Added `<SpeedInsights />` component at the end of the `<body>` tag
  
### 3. Implementation Details
Following the official Vercel Speed Insights documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/speed-insights/quickstart):
- Used the Next.js App Router integration pattern (`@vercel/speed-insights/next`)
- Placed the component inside the body tag after all other content
- This follows the recommended pattern for Next.js 13.5+ with App Router

## Framework Details
- **Framework**: Next.js 16.2.1 (App Router)
- **React Version**: 19.2.4
- **TypeScript**: Yes

## Verification
✅ Package installed successfully (372 packages added)
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ No new linting errors introduced (existing warnings/errors in other files are unrelated to this change)

## Next Steps for Deployment
To enable Speed Insights on Vercel:
1. Deploy this code to Vercel
2. Navigate to your project dashboard on Vercel
3. Go to the Speed Insights tab
4. Click "Enable" to activate the feature
5. After the next deployment, Speed Insights will begin collecting performance data

## Notes
- The SpeedInsights component is lightweight and will only load on Vercel deployments
- In local development, it will not affect performance
- Data collection will begin automatically once enabled in the Vercel dashboard
